=Description=

“This talk gives some background to the setting up of 091 Labs, Galway's hackerspace, and also more generally about open spaces for creative collaboration and the principle of doocracy.

Declan Elliott has been an early pioneer in the emerging field of facilitation over the last decade. After working in business development and general management roles within Grand Metropolitan and Jardine Matheson across Asia Pacific, Europe and the US, he struck out on his own in 1998. Since then, he has focused on the evolving Internet space and its transformation of organisations' internal and external communications.”


